            h3 What to Expect
            p
              | When injected, the vein disappears, but then almost immediately becomes red and inflamed. The leg can
              | ache after treatment and this is a consequence of the irritant liquid working. The inflammation settles
              | over a period of days and the vein then becomes scarred and shrinks over weeks. It should settle
              | completely by six weeks. A final result may take up to six months.

